    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's helpful. i guess i'm just thinking about the idea of a \"protector\" or \"guardian\" for his assets. it feels like someone is supposed to be watching over the hoard of stuff he's worked his whole life for, so he doesn't lose it all to some bad actor. is there a way to make that \"guarding\" part more specific in the document?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While you can include specific duties or reporting requirements in a power of attorney, the English-speaking legal system generally does not have a formal \"asset guardian\" who oversees the agent's actions, as the agent also serves as the guardian of your estate while incapacitated. Instead, the most effective protections are creating a detailed trust with an independent trustee and possibly adding \"durable blind trusts\" to disengage your dad from any involvement while his health declines. For additional layers of security, consider hiring a professional fiduciary or joint accountant to handle the finances yourself.",
      "source": "target",
